==English==
===Pronunciation===
*(''UK''): klō''th''z'līn, /ˈkləʊðzlaɪn/, /<tt>"kl@UDzlaIn</tt>/
*(''US''): klō''th''z'līn, /ˈkloʊðzlaɪn/, /<tt>"kloUDzlaIn</tt>/

===Noun===
'''clothesline''' (''plural'' '''clotheslines''')

====Alternative spellings====
'''clothes line''' (''UK'')

#A rope or cord tied up outdoors to hang clothes on so they can dry
#:''Hang this towel out on the clothesline for me.''

====Translations====
{{top}}
*Dutch: [[wasdraad]] ''m'', [[waslijn]] ''f''
{{mid}}
*German: [[Wäscheleine]] ''f''
*Spanish: [[cuerda]] ''f'' para tender la [[ropa]]
{{bottom}}

===Transitive verb===
{{en-infl-reg-other-e|clotheslin|e||}}

#To knock (a person) over by striking his or her upper body or neck with one's arm, as if he or she had run into a low clothesline.
#:''A popular [[wrestling]] move is to clothesline your [[opponent]] onto the mat.''

